        <h1>Grilled Cheese Sandwiches with Bacon and Tomatoes Recipe</h1>
        
        <h2>Contents:</h2>
        
        <ol>
            <li>4 slices of Bread</li>
            <li>4 slices of Bacon</li>
            <li>Tomatoes</li>
            <li>Cheese</li>
            <li>5 tablespoon of butter</li>
            
        </ol>
        
        <h2 id="?"></h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 10 minute</li>
            <li>Serves: 2</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Directions</th>
                
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p>Spread about 1 tablespoon butter into the bottom of a large skillet (or just leave some fat in the pan from the bacon).
Spread 1 tablespoon (can use more) onto one side of each slice of bread.
Place the 4 slices of bread butter-side down onto a large skillet or flat grill.
Top with 1 slice of cheese, 2 slices of tomato and 2 slices cooked bacon, then 1 more slice of cheese.
Cover with a slice of bread (butter-side facing outside).
Fry over medium turning once with a spatula until golden brown on both sides.



</p>
        
